sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client<br/>(in-cluster service)
    participant Proxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Upstream as Upstream Application<br/>(localhost) HTTP

    Note over Client, Upstream: Flow 1: Authenticated Request Proxying

    Client->>Proxy: HTTPS :8443<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / Client Cert / OIDC JWT
    Note right of Proxy: Path allow-list check<br/>(--ignore-paths bypass)

    alt Bearer Token Authentication
        Proxy->>K8sAPI: POST /apis/authentication.k8s.io/v1/tokenreviews<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
        K8sAPI-->>Proxy: TokenReview Response<br/>(authenticated user info, 2min cache)
    else OIDC JWT Authentication
        Note right of Proxy: Validate JWT locally<br/>using cached JWKS keys
    else x509 Client Certificate
        Note right of Proxy: Validate client cert<br/>against --client-ca-file
    end

    Proxy->>K8sAPI: POST /apis/authorization.k8s.io/v1/subjectaccessreviews<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Proxy: SubjectAccessReview Response<br/>(allowed / denied)

    alt Authorized
        Note right of Proxy: Inject auth headers<br/>(X-Remote-User, X-Remote-Group, X-Remote-Extra-*)
        Proxy->>Upstream: HTTP request (localhost)<br/>+ injected auth headers
        Upstream-->>Proxy: HTTP response
        Proxy-->>Client: HTTPS response :8443
    else Denied
        Proxy-->>Client: 403 Forbidden
    end

    Note over Client, Upstream: Flow 2: Prometheus Metrics Scraping

    participant Prom as Prometheus<br/>(openshift-monitoring)<br/>prometheus-k8s SA

    Prom->>Proxy: GET /metrics HTTPS :8443<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (prometheus-k8s SA)
    Note right of Proxy: Hardcoded authorizer:<br/>unconditional allow for<br/>system:serviceaccount:<br/>openshift-monitoring:prometheus-k8s
    Proxy->>Upstream: GET /metrics (localhost HTTP)
    Upstream-->>Proxy: Metrics response (Prometheus format)
    Proxy-->>Prom: HTTPS response :8443
